)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-30-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npacf(data$ts2)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-30-2.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe time serie 1 seems to be a $ACF(2)$-process.\n\n# Series 5\n\n## Task 5.1\n\n### A\n\n#### I\n\nThe ACF plot should have a drop at lag 3.\n\n#### II\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(\n    0:30,\n    ARMAacf(\n        ar = c(0.9, -0.5),\n        lag.max = 30\n    ),\n    type = \"h\",\n    ylab = \"ACF\"\n)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-31-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(\n    1:30,\n    ARMAacf(\n        ar = c(0.9, -0.5),\n        lag.max = 30,\n        pacf = TRUE\n    ),\n    type = \"h\",\n    ylab = \"PACF\"\n\n)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-32-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n#### III\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nr.sim1 <- arima.sim(\n    n = 200,\n    model = list(ar = c(0.9, -0.5))\n)\n```\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n#### IV\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nts.1 <- ts(r.sim1)\nplot(ts.1)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-34-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nacf(ts.1)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-35-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npacf(ts.1)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-36-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n### B\n\n#### I\n\nThe PACF plot should have a drop at lag 4.\n\n#### II\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(\n    0:30,\n    ARMAacf(\n        ar = c(0.8, -0.5, -0.4),\n        lag.max = 30\n    ),\n    type = \"h\",\n    ylab = \"ACF\"\n)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-37-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nplot(\n    1:30,\n    ARMAacf(\n        ar = c(0.8, -0.5, -0.4),\n        lag.max = 30,\n        pacf = TRUE\n    ),\n    type = \"h\",\n    ylab = \"PACF\"\n\n)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-38-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n#### III\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nr.sim1 <- arima.sim(\n    n = 200,\n    model = list(ar = c(0.8, -0.5, -0.4))\n)\n```\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n#### IV\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nts.1 <- ts(r.sim1)\nplot(ts.1)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-40-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nacf(ts.1)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-41-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\npacf(ts.1)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output-display}\n![](rtp_exercises_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-42-1.png){width=672}\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\n## Exercise 5.2\n\n### A\n\n#### I\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nroots_i <- polyroot(c(1, -0.5, -2))\nabs(roots_i)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n[1] 0.5930703 0.8430703\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe process is not stationary.\n\n#### II\n\n\n\n\n\n\n::: {.cell}\n\n```{.r .cell-code}\nroots_ii <- polyroot(c(1, -1))\nabs(roots_ii)\n```\n\n::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}\n\n```\n[1] 1\n```\n\n\n:::\n:::\n\n\n\n\n\n\nThe process is not stationary.\n\n### B\n\n$$\n0.5 + x = 1\n$$\n\n$$\nx = 1 - 0.5\n$$\n\n$$\nx = 0.5\n$$\n\nThe process is stationary for $\\alpha_2 = 0.5$.\n\n### C\n\nThe condition for stationarity is $∣\\alpha∣<1$. Therefore, if $∣\\alpha∣≥1$, the root $z=\\dfrac{1}{\\alpha}$​ lies either on the unit circle $(∣z∣=1)$ or inside it $(∣z∣≤1)$. This mathematically confirms that the model is non-stationary in these cases.\n",
